  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Frameworks:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious financial transactions\n\n3. Key Regulatory Approaches:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Enhanced financial transparency\n- International information sharing\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Regulatory sanctions\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income and track potential financial crimes.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
